# $Header: /var/cvsroot/gentoo-x86/kde-base/smoke/ChangeLog,v 1.10 2005/03/18 16:51:36 morfic Exp $

  18 Mar 2005; Daniel Goller <morfic@gentoo.org> smoke-3.4.0.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc

  13 Mar 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> smoke-3.4.0.ebuild:
  KDE 3.4.0 ebuilds. Note that the tarballs won't be officially released for a
  few more days.

  28 Feb 2005; Caleb Tennis <caleb@gentoo.org>
  +files/no_knotifywidgetbase.diff:
  Patch gets rid of knotifywidgetbase.h, which isn't exported

  27 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> :
  Ebuild for 3.4.0 RC1.

  19 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> smoke-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Disabled enable-final in smoke-3.3.1. It was disabled in 3.4.0_beta2 some
  time ago. Building smoke with enable-final is possible, but takes at least
  1.5GB RAM.

  11 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> smoke-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Added x86 (stable) keyword.

*smoke-3.4.0_beta2 (05 Feb 2005)

  05 Feb 2005; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> +smoke-3.4.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Ebuild for 3.4.0_beta2. Note that beta2 has NOT been released as of this
  date. This ebuild is for inside testing by the KDE team, and is of course
  package.masked.

  10 Dec 2004; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org> files/no-gtk-glib-check.diff,
  smoke-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Fixed compile failure when gtk is not installed.

  25 Nov 2004; Sven Wegener <swegener@gentoo.org> :
  Added missing digest entries.

*smoke-3.3.1 (06 Nov 2004)

  06 Nov 2004; Dan Armak <danarmak@gentoo.org>
  +files/no-gtk-glib-check.diff, +files/parallel-make.diff,
  +smoke-3.3.1.ebuild:
  Initial version of the split-up kdebindings ebuilds. Cf.
  kde-metaebuilds.berlios.de. This is a project to split the monolithic kde
  ebuilds into separate ebuilds for separate applications. These ebuilds are
  packaged.masked at first, pending testing.

